The '''1982 Bristol Open''' was a [[tennis]] tournament played on [[grass court]]s that was part of the [[1982 Volvo Grand Prix]]. It was played at [[Bristol]] in [[Great Britain]] and began on June 14, 1982.

==Champions==
===Men's Singles===
{{main|1982 Bristol Open - Singles}}
{{flagicon|AUS}} '''[[John Alexander (tennis)|John Alexander]]''' defeated {{flagicon|USA}} [[Tim Mayotte]] 6&ndash;3, 6&ndash;4
* It was Alexander's 2nd title of the year and the 31st of his career.

===Men's Doubles===
{{main|1982 Bristol Open - Doubles}}
{{flagicon|USA}} '''[[Tim Gullikson]]''' / {{flagicon|USA}} '''[[Tom Gullikson]]''' defeated {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Mark Edmondson]] / {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Kim Warwick]] 6&ndash;4, 7&ndash;6
* It was Tim Gullikson's 2nd title of the year and the 13th of his career. It was Tom Gullikson's 3rd title of the year and the 11th of his career.

